data.text:
Cooper Top Marks

2024

Outdoor

Earned a third-place finish in the men’s shot put with a 16.80-meter (55-1.5) mark (Bulldog Relays)

Recorded a ninth-place finish in the men’s shot put with a 16.73-meter (54-10.75) throw (Battle on the Bayou)

Finished seventh in the men’s shot put with a 16.84-meter (55-3) toss (Crimson Tide Invitational)

Indoor

Concluded the field section of the meet for Alabama with a top-five finish in the men's shot put (fourth | 16.08m | 52-9.25) (Samford Invitational)

2022-23

Outdoor

Competed in one meet for the Crimson Tide, logging a top-22 finish in the shot put at the Don Kirby Invitational

Indoor

Represented Alabama in three meets, highlighted by a fifth-place finish in the shot put at the Samford Invite

2021-22

Outdoor

Finished 13th in the shot put at the SEC Championships

Posted a career-best throw of 17.05 meters in the shot put at the Tom Jones Memorial

2020-21

Outdoor

Recorded a career-best mark of 16.62m (54-6.5) in the shot put at the LSU Alumni Gold

Placed 13th in the shot put at the SEC Championships

Competed in shot put at the Crimson Tide Invitational with a mark of 16.00m

Placed tenth in shot put at the Pepsi Florida Relays with a mark of 15.71m

Secured a fifth place finish in shot put at the Al Schmidt Bulldog Relays with a mark of 15.85m

Opened the outdoor season with a eighth place finish in shot put with a mark of 15.40m at the Tiger Track Classic

Indoor

Competed in shot put (15.67m) at the SEC Indoor Track and Field Championships

Traveled to the Tyson Invitational to compete in shot put with a mark of 15.98m

Competed in shot put at the South Carolina Invitational with a mark of 15.62m

Recorded a fourth place finish in shot put at the Carolina Challenge with a mark of 15.75m

Opened his collegiate career competing in shot put at the Vanderbilt Invitational with a mark of 15.26m

Prep Highlights

Local Alabama product that holds the No.1 mark in the state in men's indoor weight throw (53-9.75)

Ranks second in the state and 10th nationally in indoor shot put with an effort of 60-10.5 (17.9m)

Named five-time All-American and state champion in shot put and discus

Tabbed USATF National Champion in shot put

Coached by Jocquette Carroll, Katrina Culbreath and DiShon Benjamin at Dothan High School

Personal

Born March 27, 2002

Son of Chris and Carrie Cooper

Has one sibling, Christopher

Majoring in kinesiology
